"The plan was always to open a Michigan location," said Thompson, 29, a filmmaker and father of five based in Monroe, Michigan. 

"Last year, we found a great location in Ohio that we couldn't pass up, and I think that was the only driving factor in opening in Ohio first. We've been so excited to [open a restaurant in Michigan](https://www.foxnews.com/category/us/us-regions/midwest/michigan) for a very long time."

The new venue, expected to open in April in the Mall of Monroe, will offer items exclusive to that location, Thompson added.

The Ohio location also serves themed drinks with names tied to [true-crime lore,](https://www.foxnews.com/category/us/true-crime) including a cocktail inspired by Charles Manson. 

