It claims it is the only restaurant "where you can eat a meal and then hold [a human skull](https://www.foxnews.com/category/science/archaeology)," referring to its museum that also displays bones, taxidermy and true-crime memorabilia.

The themed restaurant has fueled both intrigue and discomfort. 

